The Msambweni by-election is done and dusted. Many feign surprise and read too much into the issue, according to their own leaning. In this atmosphere, different opinions have been advanced without consideration of the past.
History is stubborn and only armed with that analysis can we unveil the truth about South Coast politics. The not-so-independent candidate Feisal Bader beat the heavy favourite, ODM’s Omar Boga, but this is not the first time such upsets have occurred in Kwale.



