Using the shark, Shirikisho Party symbol, Mwakwere nicknamed himself Dzipapa (the shark) creating a niche for himself becoming a strong political personality at the Coast at the time.
Both Mwakwere and Rai had all along been strongly opposed to interference from Mombasa leadership, a belief that saw the Kinango MP decamp and successfully defend his seat on Jubilee’s The National Alliance wing in 2013.
Ditch ODM
For the 20 years he served as an MP, Rai believed that the easiest candidate to beat was whosoever associates his race with Mombasa. It is the same belief that saw Mvurya ditch ODM for Jubilee in the run-up to the 2017 General Election.
 ODM’s presence was in Msambweni via Suleiman Dori and Mwanyoha in 2013 as long serving Ford-K councillor Khatib Mwashetani became the MP for newly created Lunga Lunga Constituency on the Moses Wetangula-led party.   In 2017, Mvurya and Mwashetani sailed through via Jubilee, Kassim Sawa Tandaza becoming Matuga MP on an ANC ticket while ODM had Benjamin Tayari (Kinango), Dori (Msambweni), Woman Rep Zuleikha Hassan and Senator Issa Boy.





With a well-structured bursary and the first overseas scholarship programme ever witnessed in Coast since independence, Mvurya has become a strong political personality in Kwale to the extent that “his word is final”.



